    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with **Kyle Tucker** headlining the offense, boasting an elite 85.90 score. Facing Sugano, **Kyle Tucker** benefits from a massive 14% park factor boost and strong situational hitting metrics, making him our primary engine for power and speed. He is joined in the must-start tier by **Gunnar Henderson** (79.59), whose leadoff spot against Bibee provides the highest floor for run production, and **Andy Pages** (72.14), who leverages the same favorable park conditions as **Kyle Tucker** to climb into the strong-start category despite his lower position in the order. **Josh Lowe** (71.68) remains an essential component of our strategy; against the porous 7.83 xERA of Matt Waldron, his high-efficiency projection against the platoon makes him a vital contributor to our stolen base targets.\n\nOur most difficult decision came at the UTIL spot, where **Marcell Ozuna** (59.24) barely held off **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (57.57). While **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** possesses superior xwOBA metrics, the optimizer favored **Marcell Ozuna** due to his more favorable SP matchup and cleaner platoon dynamics for today\u2019s specific environment. We are closely monitoring **Miguel Vargas** and **Jackson Merrill**, both of whom carry \"Lineup Pending\" tags; should either shift down in the batting order or get scratched, we will re-evaluate our bench depth. While **Luis Robert Jr.** and **Brady House** offer tantalizing upside, particularly with **Brady House** playing against the slower delivery of Webb\u2014a key indicator for our stolen base needs\u2014the higher baseline efficiency of our current starters keeps them sidelined for this rotation.",
